test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 1 == 28
 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7a1be34b8d80>([28])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7a1be34b8d80> = [[1, 28], [1, 28, 1], [28], [28, 1], [1, 28], [1, 28, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7a1be34b8d80>([1, 28])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7a1be34b8d80> = [[1, 28], [1, 28, 1], [28], [28, 1], [1, 28], [1, 28, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7a1be34b8d80>([28, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7a1be34b8d80> = [[1, 28], [1, 28, 1], [28], [28, 1], [1, 28], [1, 28, 1], ...].count
